Mothers of the accused packed the public gallery on Tuesday &amp; gasped when the case was postponed to 18 January. CAPE TOWN - Relatives of eight young men accused of the rape of a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga seemed disappointed by yet another postponement in the matter.The group, arrested last month, made a brief appearance in the Wynberg Magistrates Court on Tuesday.Mothers of the accused packed the public gallery and gasped when the case was postponed to 18 January for a formal bail application.Visibly happy to see their family members, the men blew kisses and waved as they descended to the court s holding cells.One of the accused is believed to have abducted the victim at gunpoint while she was walking along Robert Sobukwe Road. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)